description:
This first volume collects Marvel Library the first seven numbers of Daredevil USA. In the first issue we witness the arrival of the character, created by Stan Lee and Bill Everett, at which tells its particular origin and the circumstances that made a hero Matt Murdock disfrazado.Y, in the latest issue, on the hand, shows the work of legendary Wally Wood, who managed to refine the character image, to give it the red suit that has characterized it since.

Also here, this first volume of the Library Marvel: Daredevil also includes the first appearances of characters as important as Karen Page, Franklin "Foggy" Nelson (office mates Matt Murdock) and Mr. Fear and villains like the Owl, which eventually becoming common in the collection.
name: El origen de Daredevil

description:
This volume of Library Marvel: Daredevil is divided from a artistic standpoint into two distinct parts.

The first part contains the numbers that form the fundamental stage of John Romita Sr. and artist of this collection. In them, this great solo artist and draws pages of Daredevil, demonstrating his talent.

And at the end of this volume ... Gene Colan. The stage cartoonist par excellence of Man Without Fear.

description: For over fifty years, Barbie has helped young girls come of age in the midst of an ever-changing social climate, but what do we really know about her? Female Force: Ruth Handler tells the story of how America's favorite fashion doll emerged from the seedy underworld of German sex symbols and cigarette shop gag gifts to become one of history's most iconic women.

volume.name: Female Force: Ruth Handler, Creator of Barbie

description: In a story that takes place in the Batman's early years, the Dark Knight comes face-to-face with the Reaper, a vigilante who has become judge, jury, and executioner on the criminal underworld. As Bruce Wayne pursues a romantic relationship with Rachel Caspian, the Batman pursues the Reaper. When Batman strikes a deal with Gotham's criminal element he comes face-to-face with Joe Chill, the man who murdered Bruce Wayne's parents. In order to catch the deadly Reaper, Batman must team-up with the last person on Earth he wants to.
